- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses minimum description length (MDL) criteria for model selection, which is a common approach in machine learning. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper deals with constructing network models from underlying data. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses predictive tasks and model selection, which are common topics in AI. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the use of parsimonious models to avoid overfitting, which is a common concern in neural networks.
